      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Critical] Line 3897: validate() only verifies that HEAD and its root tree exist, but a repository can still be corrupted with missing subtrees/blobs or parent commits while passing this check. That would still leave later history/file walking operations failing and could preserve the fetch/merge retry loop this change is meant to avoid. Walk the HEAD tree and, if conversation operations depend on history traversal, the reachable commits as well. For example:\n```suggestion\n    // Verify the full tree reachable from HEAD, not only the root tree object.\n    git_tree* tree_ptr \u003d nullptr;\n    if (git_commit_tree(\u0026tree_ptr, commit.get()) \u003c 0)\n        return false;\n    GitTree tree {tree_ptr};\n    git_diff_options opts \u003d GIT_DIFF_OPTIONS_INIT;\n    // Alternatively use git_revwalk + git_commit_tree/git_tree_walk to ensure every\n    // reachable commit/tree/blob needed by the conversation can be loaded.\n```\nUse the existing RAII wrappers/patterns in this file to implement a complete object reachability check.",
